race.comment: HELL OF A PRINCE (13) went forward last start over 1900m at this track and held on well for second, beaten 0.6 lengths. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. The well-related PIMPERNEL (14) (half to 2xG2 winner Miss Rose De Lago) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when 1.3 lengths away in third over 1900m at this circuit when he was always up in the leading division. Likely improver with strong prospects. IMAGINA (3) recorded a strong maiden win over 1890m at Toowoomba last time, getting there by 1.75 lengths. Jumps from a wide draw but another bold showing is expected. BORN TO BE ALIVE (6) went forward from the low draw last time before fading to finish fourth over 1900m here. Can figure in the finish.
